examples.en: Her words contained an implicit threat.
The report contained a number of factual errors.
The discharge from the wound contained pus.
The caves contained many prehistoric artifacts.
This book contained the opening letter of our professor.
The proposed changes are contained in a policy statement.
The room contained the company's large computer installation.
The story contained some awkward writing.
The signal contained thousands of bits of information.
The hastily put together report contained a lot of errors.
His canteen contained a small tea-service and many other useful things.
A metallurgist did an assay on the metal and determined it contained nickel.
Jansen's review contained several inaccuracies.
The space contained close alleys and open walks.
The box contained a taper to light each firework.
How big is the angle contained by these two sides?
The cell contained an iron bedframe bolted to the floor.
The letter contained information about Boulestin's legal affairs.
The insurance policy covers the building and any fixtures contained therein.
Too big to be extinguished at once, the forest fires at best could be contained.
A certain conclusion is implicitly contained in certain premises explicitly stated.
I gave the ingredients list a quick check to see if the cereal contained any sugar.
His pockets contained a motley collection of coins, movie ticket stubs, and old candies.
The device, which contained 400lbs of explosive, was made safe by army bomb disposal experts.
